{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS (0 blocking, 9 advisory). Triage — all valid, folded into implementation: (1) f7ca28: place default-assignee fallback at TOP of claim_compute, before the parent-cascade recursion, so cascaded parent claims inherit the default. (2) ffea27: use None sentinel for omitted --assignee; explicit --assignee '' clears (explicit wins), only omitted falls back to default. (3) f9ea30: claim_cli captures claim_compute's return and uses result['assignee'] for JSON + report suffix. (4) f27285: claim writes a LOCAL assignee (EDIT event); resolution to a Jira accountId happens at reconcile (co-landing unify fix 544e). Default must be Jira-resolvable -> configuring joeoakhart@navapbc.com (the resolvable email, not a bare handle); jira.user kept separate (auth user vs work-attribution) but documented as usually the same. (5) f2460f: canonical env name = REBAR_DEFAULT_ASSIGNEE in _CANONICAL_ENV_NAMES. (6) cascade path covered by tests. RED tests precede implementation."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782756137733255001,"uuid":"c6ace7a5-b85c-4b99-b4f7-139373afd7d2"}